\section{Pronouns}

\begin{tabular}{ll}
  Independent & Attached\\
  \midrule

  ana   & -i/-ni (object)\\
inti  & -ak\\
inta  & -ik\\
huwe  & -u\\
hiye  & -a\\
niHna & -na\\
hum   & -un\\
hunne & -kun\\

\end{tabular}

Attached pronouns are

\begin{itemize}
  \item direct objects: \textit{katbt-u} 'I~wrote~it'
  \item indirect objects, with \textit{-l-}, \textit{katabt-l-u} 'I~write~for~him'
  \item possessors: \textit{ktaab-u} 'his~book'
\end{itemize}

(on verbs) and possessors (on nouns).

\section{Perpositions}

\begin{tabular}{lrp{4cm}}

  bi-  & in, at  (with noun)\\
  fii- & in, at  (with pronoun)\\
  ʿa-  & to\\
  min  & from\\
  ill-  & for (ownership, with pronouns)\\
  li-  & for (ownership, with nouns)\\
  ʿind  & with\\

\end{tabular}

\section{Quenstion words}

\begin{tabular}{>{\itshape}ll}

  ween & where\\
  miin & who\\
  kiif & how\\
  shuu & what\\
  eemta & when\\

\end{tabular}
  
\section{Verbs}

\begin{tabular}{l
  >{\itshape}r@{\textcolor{gray}{\itshape ktib}}>{\itshape}l
  @{\quad\textcolor{gray}{\itshape katab}}>{\itshape}l
  }

  & \multicolumn{2}{l}{Non-past}&\multicolumn{1}{l}{Non-past}\\

  \midrule

  I          & i  &    & t\\
  yous (ms.) & ti &    & t\\
  you (fs.)  & ti & i & ti\\
  he         & yi &    & \\
  she        & ti &    & it\\
  we         & ni &    & na\\
  you (pl.)  & ti & u & tu\\
  they       & yi & u & u\\

\end{tabular}

The pronoun may be omitted. The verb is always preceded by one, and only one, of the following:

\begin{tabular}{rl}
  \textit{b-}&indicative: \textit{bektib}. Note: \textit{**m**-niktib}\\
  \textit{ʿam} &indicative: \textit{ʿam iktib}\\
  \textit{Ha-/raH} &future: \textit{raH iktib}\\
  Aux. verb& eg. \textit{biddu, biyHibb, kaat}: \textit{biddi ektib}\\
\end{tabular}

\section{Pseudo verbs}

The following are not inflected as verbs but takes verbal negation with \textit{maa}. \textit{bidd-} and \textit{ʿind} take pronominal subjects in attached form: \textit{biddu} 'he\ wants', \textit{ʿindu} 'he\ has.'

\begin{itemize}
  \item \textit{bidd-} 'want'
  \item \textit{ʿind} 'has'
\end{itemize}

\section{Standard to Syrian Arabic sound rules}

\begin{tabular}{l@{~→~}ll@{~→~}l}


  ay & ee & bayt & beet \\
  aw & oo & yawm & yoom \\
  q  & ʾ  & qaal & ʾaal \\
  th & t  & thalatha & tlaate* \\
  dh & d  & haadha & haada* \\
  DH & D  & DHuhr & Duhr \\

\end{tabular}

For loans fro Standard Arabic \textit{th} and\ \textit{dh} becomes \textit{s} and\ \textit{z}: \textit{musaqqaf}, \textit{iza}.



